data.content: Over the past five years, India's nominal GDP has risen steadily from about $2.84 trillion in 2019 to roughly $3.64 trillion in 2023. This represents an increase of around $0.80 trillion, or roughly a 28% growth over the period, corresponding to an average annual growth rate of about 7% when measured in current U.S. dollars.
